{"word":"ἐρατός","slug":"ἐρατός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐρατός</b></el> <el>(ἐρᾰτός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἐράω</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>lovely, charming</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: —<a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>ἐρατὸν κιθαρίζειν</el> <b>Hhymn.</b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>beloved</i>, <b>Tyrtae.</b><p/></div>"}]}